summary:
“Bran had always liked the godswood, even before, but of late he found 
himself drawn to it more and more. Even the heart tree...
body: “Bran had always liked the godswood, even before, but of late he found himself drawn to it more and more. Even the heart tree no longer scared him the way it used to. The deep red eyes carved into the pale trunk still watched him, yet somehow he took comfort from that now. The gods were looking over him, he told himself; the old gods, gods of the Starks and the First Men and the children of the forest, his father’s gods. He felt safe in their sight, and the deep silence of the trees helped him think. Bran had been thinking a lot since his fall; thinking, and dreaming, and talking with the gods.”  - George R. R. Martin, A Game of Thrones

summary: I dont understand Jon going back to the wall and not just because i hate it. I was under the impression that the Wall...
body:
I dont understand Jon going back to the wall and not just because i hate it. I was under the impression that the Wall fell…like it was a major issue. 

So exactly where is he going to go? Where the Wall once stood? Is he going to go find Tormund and Ghost? Is he going to take up residence at Hard Home (it seems like a castle free-for-all lately)? Where is he going to go because there is no Wall for him to go back to unless he builds his own…or maybe he works with Bran to make a new one or something, but they dont talk about Bran the Builder in the show so it doesnt have the foreshadowing…
